# Running coconut-app on a Physical iPhone

## Environment constraints
- Corporate network (Databricks) blocks `registry.npmjs.org` and `repo1.maven.org` via `/etc/hosts`
- Use `--registry https://registry.npmmirror.com` for all `npm install` commands
- Hermes prebuilt binaries must be downloaded manually (see below)
- Device-to-device LAN is blocked — use `--tunnel` for Metro

## Device IDs
- **xcodebuild destination**: `id=00008150-000C5C8E3601401C`
- **devicectl UDID**: `E7DF27D8-000A-51D5-A001-42797CBAB155`
- **Bundle ID (dev build)**: `com.coconut.app.aaran`

## Step 1 — Fix app.config.js before every build
The `"react-native-reanimated"` expo plugin crashes the build on Node 20. Remove it before building (it's already applied to the native layer):
```js
// In app.config.js plugins array — remove this line:
"react-native-reanimated",
```

## Step 2 — Build the native app
```bash
cd ~/coconut-app/ios
RCT_HERMES_V1_ENABLED=1 xcodebuild \
  -workspace Coconut.xcworkspace \
  -scheme Coconut \
  -configuration Debug \
  -destination 'id=00008150-000C5C8E3601401C' \
  build
```
Incremental builds finish in ~15-30s. First build takes longer.

If `pod install` is needed (new deps), Hermes tarballs must be pre-downloaded:
```bash
# Get IP for blocked maven host
MAVEN_IP=$(nslookup repo1.maven.org 8.8.8.8 | grep Address | tail -1 | awk '{print $2}')
curl --resolve "repo1.maven.org:443:$MAVEN_IP" -L \
  "https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/com/facebook/react/react-native-artifacts/0.78.1/react-native-artifacts-0.78.1-hermes-framework-dSYM-debug.tar.gz" \
  -o /tmp/hermes-debug.tar.gz
# Then:
HERMES_ENGINE_TARBALL_PATH=/tmp/hermes-debug.tar.gz pod install
```

## Step 3 — Install on device
```bash
xcrun devicectl device install app \
  --device 00008150-000C5C8E3601401C \
  ~/Library/Developer/Xcode/DerivedData/Coconut-*/Build/Products/Debug-iphoneos/Coconut.app
```

## Step 4 — Launch on device
```bash
xcrun devicectl device process launch \
  --device 00008150-000C5C8E3601401C \
  com.coconut.app.aaran
```

## Step 5 — Start Metro with tunnel (required — LAN is blocked)
```bash
# Install ngrok if needed (once):
npm install -g @expo/ngrok@^4.1.0 --registry https://registry.npmmirror.com

cd ~/coconut-app
npx expo start --tunnel --clear
```
Get the tunnel URL:
```bash
curl -s http://localhost:4040/api/tunnels | python3 -c \
  "import sys,json; [print(t['public_url']) for t in json.load(sys.stdin)['tunnels'] if 'http://' in t['public_url']]"
```
Enter the URL manually in the app's "No development servers found" screen.

## Trusting the dev certificate (once per install)
Settings → General → VPN & Device Management → your Apple ID → Trust

## Key files
- `.env` — contains all `EXPO_PUBLIC_*` vars, `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://coconut-app.dev`
- `ios/Podfile.properties.json` — `expo.jsEngine` must be `"hermes"`
- Hermes tarballs cached at `/tmp/hermes-debug.tar.gz` and `/tmp/hermes-release.tar.gz`
